text: Governors Point is a new enclave of 16 waterfront homes which will be designed by Omer Arbel. Just off Chuckanut Drive south of Bellingham, WA, the project sits on a pristine peninsula jutting into the Salish Sea. All homes will share a rigorous architectural language, which extends throughout the project, including private roads, gates, and other infrastructure. Buffered by a 100-acre nature reserve, the homes enjoy a grandfathered 75' saltwater setback and vistas overlooking the San Juan Islands. Each dwelling, on a +/- 1 acre lot, will be personalized by discerning buyers who appreciate ambitious design in intimate harmony with nature. San Juan Island lifestyle without the hassle of the ferry system. Welcome to lot 2 at Governors Point.

Waterfront at its finest! Designed by renowned architect Nils Finne and constructed by Emerald Builders, this AIA award-winning home rests atop the bluff at Boundary Ridge. Finne--dedicated to Crafted Modernism with a clear understanding of the importance of weaving the landscape and the light with the structure has created a waterfront home which is truly a piece of art. Capturing the sunlight from every angle, the inverted roof, fir beam fan trusses, stone plinth, clerestory windows, and innumerable design features command the beauty of the view. A one of a kind masterpiece--crafted like no others. Sought after waterfront location offers the finest of island views, truly breathtaking sunsets, Zen serenity and city lights.
